{"parse":{"title":"CERN ritual hoax","pageid":58018766,"revid":860185293,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Cern_ritual.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c7/Cern_ritual.jpg/220px-Cern_ritual.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"123\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c7/Cern_ritual.jpg/330px-Cern_ritual.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c7/Cern_ritual.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"421\" data-file-height=\"236\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Cern_ritual.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Frame from the video depicting men in cloaks gathered around the statue of Shiva</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>CERN ritual</b> is a video that depicts an alleged occult ritual occurring in the grounds of <a href=\"/wiki/CERN\" title=\"CERN\">CERN</a>, a European nuclear research organization. The video showed several men dressed in black cloaks surrounding a statue of the Hindu deity <a href=\"/wiki/Shiva\" title=\"Shiva\">Shiva</a> and apparently stabbing a woman in a mock human sacrifice. The video ended with the man filming crying out and running away.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The video went viral in August 2016 and fueled many <a href=\"/wiki/Conspiracy_theories\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Conspiracy theories\">conspiracy theories</a> concerning CERN. CERN later stated in its FAQ that the video was \"fiction\" and the actions violated its professional guidelines.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reactions\">Reactions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=CERN_ritual_hoax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Reactions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A CERN spokesperson stated that the video was a hoax and that no one was actually harmed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The enactment was performed without any official permission. CERN stated that it \"doesn't tolerate this kind of spoof\" and that it can \"give rise to misunderstandings about the scientific nature of our work\u201d.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The video caused a lot of controversy and ignited conspiracy theories about CERN's activities. Given that the ritual was performed in front of a statue of a deity, many believed the ritual was satanic in nature. This further fueled theories that CERN's goal was to use their <a href=\"/wiki/Large_Hadron_Collider\" title=\"Large Hadron Collider\">Large Hadron Collider</a> to create a portal to hell, summon the <a href=\"/wiki/Antichrist\" title=\"Antichrist\">antichrist</a>, or resurrect the ancient gods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=CERN_ritual_hoax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Staff and agencies in Geneva (2016-08-18). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/aug/18/fake-human-sacrifice-filmed-at-cern-with-pranking-scientists-suspected\">\"Fake human sacrifice filmed at Cern, with pranking scientists suspected\"</a>. <i>the Guardian</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-07-29</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=the+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=Fake+human+sacrifice+filmed+at+Cern%2C+with+pranking+scientists+suspected&amp;rft.date=2016-08-18&amp;rft.au=Staff+and+agencies+in+Geneva&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fscience%2F2016%2Faug%2F18%2Ffake-human-sacrifice-filmed-at-cern-with-pranking-scientists-suspected&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACERN+ritual+hoax\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Mazza, Ed (2016-08-19). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/cern-devil-worship-sacrifice-video_us_57b6856ce4b00d9c3a16cd67\">\"Video Of 'Satanic Ritual' At World's Most Famous Physics Lab Is A Hoax\"</a>. <i>Huffington Post</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-07-29</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Huffington+Post&amp;rft.atitle=Video+Of+%27Satanic+Ritual%27+At+World%27s+Most+Famous+Physics+Lab+Is+A+Hoax&amp;rft.date=2016-08-19&amp;rft.aulast=Mazza&amp;rft.aufirst=Ed&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.com%2Fentry%2Fcern-devil-worship-sacrifice-video_us_57b6856ce4b00d9c3a16cd67&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACERN+ritual+hoax\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite